summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling previous resolutions, particularly 2360 (2017), and statements on the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC),

Reaffirming commitment to DRC's sovereignty, independence, unity, and territorial integrity,

Noting the final report (S/2019/469) of the Group of Experts on the DRC,

Reiterating the need for the DRC Government to investigate and bring to justice those responsible for killing two Group of Experts members and four Congolese nationals,

Determining the situation in DRC continues to threaten international peace and security,

Acting under Chapter VII:

1. Renews until 1 July 2020 measures set out in paragraphs 1-6 of resolution 2293 (2016);
2. Reaffirms measures in paragraph 5 of resolution 2293 (2016) apply to individuals and entities designated by the Committee;
3. Extends until 1 August 2020 the Group of Experts' mandate, reviews it by 1 July 2020, and requests the Secretary-General to re-establish the Group;
4. Requests the Group of Experts to provide a mid-term report by 30 December 2019, a final report by 15 June 2020, and monthly updates to the Committee;
5. Reaffirms reporting provisions in resolution 2360 (2017);
6. Recalls Committee guidelines and calls on Member states to use them;
7. Requests the Group of Experts to circulate proposed updates to the DRC Sanctions List;
8. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
